==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sudoriferous
<hw>Su`dor*if"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sudor</ets> sweat + <ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Producing, or secreting, sweat;
sudoriparous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sudoriferous glands</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>,
<cd>small convoluted tubular glands which are situated in the
subcutaneous tissues and discharge by minute orifices in the surface of
the skin; the sweat glands.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sudorific</ent>⟦br⟧
